In the case of C8H17N3O, the corresponding SMILES expression would be "CC(C)CCCC(C)N(=O)=O". This notation represents the connectivity of atoms within the molecule, with each element represented by its atomic symbol and bonds indicated by specific characters. The SMILES expression provides a standardized way to represent molecular structures for computational purposes, facilitating communication and analysis in various fields such as chemistry, bioinformatics, and drug design.
